# Promote code patterns from `docs/` into `patterns/`

Whenever you **add, generate, or materially update** content under `docs/` (package digests, troubleshooting notes, API summaries, copied upstream examples, etc.):

1. **Scan the new or changed material** for fenced code, CLI output, configuration snippets, and any sections that contrast “do this” vs “avoid this,” wrong vs fixed, or gold-path vs failure.
2. **Classify** each reusable insight as either a **preferred / canonical pattern** (see `patterns/goldpath/README.md`) or an **anti-pattern, pitfall, or corrected mistake** (see `patterns/errors/README.md`).
3. **Write short pattern entries** under `patterns/goldpath/` or `patterns/errors/` when the lesson is likely to help future work—not every one-off snippet. Follow [`patterns/README.md`](../../patterns/README.md), the README in the target subfolder, and [`patterns-directory-for-agents.mdc`](./patterns-directory-for-agents.mdc); cite the source file under `docs/` and keep entries concise so other agents benefit without rereading long docs.

This complements reading `docs/` for dependencies: documentation is the working surface; `patterns/` is the durable, agent-oriented index of **gold path** (follow) and **errors** (avoid) code patterns.

Bug fixes, CI failures, and deploy issues **without** a `docs/` change still require the same promotion: follow [`document-fixes-in-patterns.mdc`](./document-fixes-in-patterns.mdc) and add paired **`patterns/errors/`** + **`patterns/goldpath/`** entries when the lesson is reusable.
